{
  "text": ", and if ω = 1, then we set Gelfand-Shilov spaces and their dual spaces can be described as projective or inductive limits of modulation spaces [CITATION_1] Theorem 3.9] . In particular, we have the following characterization of Gelfand-Shilov spaces by the means of the short-time Fourier transform. We refer to [CITATION_2] for the proof, see also [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
